AUDIENCE: So these days
when we have a problem

00:48:41.110 --> 00:48:44.310
or are trying to solve
something, we frequently

00:48:44.310 --> 00:48:47.426
go search the web or go to
YouTube, how to do this,

00:48:47.426 --> 00:48:48.050
how to do that.

00:48:48.050 --> 00:48:49.530
That could be a
little bit similar

00:48:49.530 --> 00:48:51.440
to what that [INAUDIBLE]
before me asked.

00:48:51.440 --> 00:48:56.360
Now, what's the right
thing to do here?

00:48:56.360 --> 00:48:59.120
Now, if you have a problem
and you look it up,

00:48:59.120 --> 00:49:00.830
you'll solve the
problem quickly.

00:49:00.830 --> 00:49:04.550
But then, you blocked
yourself from finding

00:49:04.550 --> 00:49:06.140
a solution yourself.

00:49:06.140 --> 00:49:10.330
But on the other hand, you
expose yourself to other ideas.

00:49:10.330 --> 00:49:11.940
This is good, as you said.

00:49:11.940 --> 00:49:13.790
If you expose yourself
to other ideas,

00:49:13.790 --> 00:49:15.710
you will come up with new ideas.

00:49:15.710 --> 00:49:18.407
But then, if you don't try
to come up with ideas--

00:49:18.407 --> 00:49:19.740
you see the contradiction there?

00:49:19.740 --> 00:49:22.550
SCOTT BERKUN: I do.

00:49:22.550 --> 00:49:24.440
I guess it's usually
not a problem

00:49:24.440 --> 00:49:26.960
because if you were
to say, decide,

00:49:26.960 --> 00:49:30.020
that you wanted to
start a company, well

00:49:30.020 --> 00:49:31.880
you'd Google, how do
I start a company?

00:49:31.880 --> 00:49:34.505
And you'd find a list of things
that you now have to go and do,

00:49:34.505 --> 00:49:35.632
like I said before.

00:49:35.632 --> 00:49:37.340
Once you start going
and do those things,

00:49:37.340 --> 00:49:39.939
you may realize or recognize
that there's a better way

00:49:39.939 --> 00:49:42.230
to do them, will be frustrated
with one of those steps,

00:49:42.230 --> 00:49:43.452
you'll seek out other ones.

00:49:43.452 --> 00:49:45.410
But most of the things
you're likely to look up

00:49:45.410 --> 00:49:49.226
as ways to solve the problem
are going to be very abstract.

00:49:49.226 --> 00:49:51.850
Like if you were to do a Google
search for how to write a book.

00:49:51.850 --> 00:49:54.230
It's going to give you some
basic construction of it,

00:49:54.230 --> 00:49:56.188
but it's not going to
tell you whether to write

00:49:56.188 --> 00:50:00.242
a novel or a thriller
or a Victorian drama.

00:50:00.242 --> 00:50:01.950
There's always going
to be a lot of space

00:50:01.950 --> 00:50:03.600
that you need to
fill out yourself.

00:50:03.600 --> 00:50:05.100
And so I guess what
I would say is--

00:50:05.100 --> 00:50:09.270
it's a very practical answer--
is do the things that actually

00:50:09.270 --> 00:50:11.209
help you produce.

00:50:11.209 --> 00:50:12.750
If you produce stuff
and you're like,

00:50:12.750 --> 00:50:17.290
my solutions and the things I
create are really boring to me,

00:50:17.290 --> 00:50:19.260
then maybe say for
the next project,

00:50:19.260 --> 00:50:21.540
I'm not going to
research anything.

00:50:21.540 --> 00:50:23.171
And experiment that way.

00:50:23.171 --> 00:50:25.670
Every project is going to be
different, especially if you're

00:50:25.670 --> 00:50:26.850
trying to do ambitious work.

00:50:26.850 --> 00:50:28.500
Every project is
going to be different

00:50:28.500 --> 00:50:30.541
and it's going to demand
different things of you,

00:50:30.541 --> 00:50:33.210
it's going to require different
techniques or skills to try.

00:50:33.210 --> 00:50:37.880
So there's no universal
answer, unfortunately.

00:50:37.880 --> 00:50:40.070
And that is the case for
a lot of these questions.

00:50:40.070 --> 00:50:43.960
A common question I get asked
is how do I know when I'm done?

00:50:43.960 --> 00:50:45.650
How do I know when I'm done?

00:50:45.650 --> 00:50:49.230
And I'm like, have you
ever consumed something

00:50:49.230 --> 00:50:53.020
like a movie or software product
or a book and you're like,

00:50:53.020 --> 00:50:54.270
this is terrible.

00:50:54.270 --> 00:50:57.220
Yet you paid money for it
and it exists in the world.

00:50:57.220 --> 00:51:00.420
Lots of finished stuff, many
people think isn't very good.

00:51:00.420 --> 00:51:01.660
Is not done.

00:51:01.660 --> 00:51:02.810
I'm sure you have arguments
with your coworkers.

00:51:02.810 --> 00:51:04.065
They're like, we need
to ship this today.

00:51:04.065 --> 00:51:05.400
And you're like, no
this is terrible.

00:51:05.400 --> 00:51:07.050
It's got all these
bugs and problems.

00:51:07.050 --> 00:51:10.650
It's inherently debatable,
when is it done.

00:51:10.650 --> 00:51:11.910
Inherently debatable.

00:51:11.910 --> 00:51:14.090
And the way you solve
those discussions

00:51:14.090 --> 00:51:15.960
is with a group of
people, some consensus

00:51:15.960 --> 00:51:18.460
on what the criteria is for
actually shipping something.

00:51:18.460 --> 00:51:19.710
And you do that with yourself.

00:51:19.710 --> 00:51:21.360
Is this essay good
enough to publish?

00:51:21.360 --> 00:51:21.942
I don't know.

00:51:21.942 --> 00:51:23.400
Is this tweet good
enough to tweet?

00:51:23.400 --> 00:51:24.109
I don't know.

00:51:24.109 --> 00:51:25.650
Some people spend
time reviewing them

00:51:25.650 --> 00:51:27.000
and they put them in
their drafts folder.

00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:29.125
Other people, you can tell,
just go blah blah blah,

00:51:29.125 --> 00:51:30.810
and push the button.

00:51:30.810 --> 00:51:31.530
Right?

00:51:31.530 --> 00:51:34.016
So is one right, is one wrong?

00:51:34.016 --> 00:51:36.390
Some of those people who just
don't really think about it

00:51:36.390 --> 00:51:37.450
much have a lot of followers.

00:51:37.450 --> 00:51:38.824
Some people who
are very precious

00:51:38.824 --> 00:51:41.310
and care a lot about high
quality don't have many.

00:51:41.310 --> 00:51:44.910
Popularity is unfair and
not based on a set criteria

00:51:44.910 --> 00:51:46.089
that we all agree on.

00:51:46.089 --> 00:51:47.880
And that's part of the
world you enter when

00:51:47.880 --> 00:51:49.200
you're doing creative work.

00:51:49.200 --> 00:51:52.650
Eiffel Tower, lots of
people at the time hated it.

00:51:52.650 --> 00:51:54.424
Were they right,
were they wrong?

00:51:54.424 --> 00:51:56.340
Depends on your point
of view and perspective.

00:51:56.340 --> 00:51:58.173
And the more creative
the work you're doing,

00:51:58.173 --> 00:52:00.990
the more subjective the
ways to evaluate it will be.

00:52:00.990 --> 00:52:02.700
So one more?

00:52:02.700 --> 00:52:04.990
Yes, sir.

