to memorize how to code,

00:53:05.520 --> 00:53:07.950
but the goal was to learn
how to make your own stuff.

00:53:07.950 --> 00:53:10.620
That the goal is to,
every quarter, every week,

00:53:10.620 --> 00:53:11.694
you've built something.

00:53:11.694 --> 00:53:13.860
And you had your criteria
for it and you evaluate it

00:53:13.860 --> 00:53:16.350
and you decide for
yourself what is good.

00:53:16.350 --> 00:53:23.090
That kind of process, that's
open-ended is central to this.

00:53:23.090 --> 00:53:27.170
And the more you focus
on grades and that--

00:53:27.170 --> 00:53:29.540
there's no way to grade
these open-ended projects.

00:53:29.540 --> 00:53:32.060
So there's a conflict between
what parents and the school

00:53:32.060 --> 00:53:34.610
system often emphasizes--
grades and tests--

00:53:34.610 --> 00:53:38.300
versus this psychology and
self-awareness and ability

00:53:38.300 --> 00:53:40.400
to choose for your
own self what's

00:53:40.400 --> 00:53:43.020
worth making, what's good,
that work against each other.

00:53:43.020 --> 00:53:44.750
So some protection
of that, I think,

00:53:44.750 --> 00:53:46.950
is the thing I would
think about first.

